<tr>
<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=an8.46&lang=pli>an8.46</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Anuruddhasutta </strong>Anuruddha and the Agreeable Deities </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>3</td>   
<td>2</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/an8_46-anuruddha-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/an8.46.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=an8.46&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Ye te bhattu abbhantarā kammantā<b>—</b>uṇṇāti vā kappāsāti vā<b>—</b>tattha dakkhā hoti analasā tatrupāyāya vīmaṁsāya samannāgatā alaṁ kātuṁ alaṁ saṁvidhātuṁ. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">She’s skilled and tireless in her husband’s household duties, such as knitting and sewing. She understands how to go about things in order to complete and organize the work. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Yo so bhattu abbhantaro antojano<b>—</b>dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā—</span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">She knows what work her husband’s domestic bondservants, employees, and workers have completed, and what they’ve left incomplete. </span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
<!-- <td><a target="_blank" href="https://voice.suttacentral.net/scv/index.html?#/sutta?search=an8.46">mp3</a></td> -->
</tr>
