<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=mn53&lang=pli>mn53</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Sekhasutta </strong>A Trainee </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>2</td>   
<td>1</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/mn53-sekha-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/mn53.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=mn53&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">seyyathidaṁ<b>—</b>ekampi jātiṁ dvepi jātiyo …pe… iti sākāraṁ sauddesaṁ anekavihitaṁ pubbenivāsaṁ anussarati, </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Yañca kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako anekavihitaṁ pubbenivāsaṁ anussarati, seyyathidaṁ<b>—</b>ekampi jātiṁ dvepi jātiyo …pe… iti sākāraṁ sauddesaṁ anekavihitaṁ pubbenivāsaṁ anussarati, idampissa hoti vijjāya; </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">A noble disciple’s knowledge includes the following: recollecting their past lives, </span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
<!-- <td><a target="_blank" href="https://voice.suttacentral.net/scv/index.html?#/sutta?search=mn53">mp3</a></td> -->
</tr>
