<tr>
<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn3.17&lang=pli>sn3.17</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Appamādasutta Kosalasaṁyuttaṁ </strong>Diligence </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>1</td>   
<td>1</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/sn3_17-pathama-appamada-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/sn3.17.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn3.17&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṁ pāṇānaṁ padajātāni, sabbāni tāni hatthipade samodhānaṁ gacchanti, hatthipadaṁ tesaṁ aggamakkhāyati<b>—</b>yadidaṁ mahantattena; </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s footprint. So an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all. </span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
