<tr>
<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn22.35&lang=pli>sn22.35</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Aññatarabhikkhusutta Khandhasaṁyuttaṁ </strong>A Mendicant </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>2</td>   
<td>0</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/sn22_35-annyatara-bhikkhu-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/sn22.35.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn22.35&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Atha kho so bhikkhu eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva<b>—</b>yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṁ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṁ<b>—</b>brahmacariyapariyosānaṁ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṁ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">Then that mendicant, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. </span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
<!-- <td><a target="_blank" href="https://voice.suttacentral.net/scv/index.html?#/sutta?search=sn22.35">mp3</a></td> -->
</tr>
