<tr>
<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn45.2&lang=pli>sn45.2</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Upaḍḍhasutta Maggasaṁyuttaṁ </strong>Half the Spiritual Life </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>5</td>   
<td>0</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/sn45_2-upaddha-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/sn45.2.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn45.2&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">“upaḍḍhamidaṁ, bhante, brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">“Sir, good friends, companions, and associates are half the spiritual life.” </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Sakalamevidaṁ, ānanda, brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">Good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Kalyāṇamittassetaṁ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṁ kalyāṇasahāyassa kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa<b>—</b>ariyaṁ aṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ bhāvessati, ariyaṁ aṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ bahulīkarissati. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Tadamināpetaṁ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṁ yathā sakalamevidaṁ brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">And here’s another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Iminā kho etaṁ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṁ yathā sakalamevidaṁ brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">This is another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.” "</span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
<!-- <td><a target="_blank" href="https://voice.suttacentral.net/scv/index.html?#/sutta?search=sn45.2">mp3</a></td> -->
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a class="freebutton" target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn45.3&lang=pli>sn45.3</a></td>
<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Sāriputtasutta Maggasaṁyuttaṁ </strong>Sāriputta </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>5</td>   
<td>0</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/sn45_3-sariputta-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/sn45.3.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn45.3&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">“sakalamidaṁ, bhante, brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">“Sir, good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life.” </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Sakalamidaṁ, sāriputta, brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">Good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Kalyāṇamittassetaṁ, sāriputta, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṁ kalyāṇasahāyassa kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa<b>—</b>ariyaṁ aṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ bhāvessati, ariyaṁ aṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ bahulīkarissati. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Tadamināpetaṁ, sāriputta, pariyāyena veditabbaṁ yathā sakalamidaṁ brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">And here’s another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life. </span>
<br class="styled">
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Iminā kho etaṁ, sāriputta, pariyāyena veditabbaṁ yathā sakalamidaṁ brahmacariyaṁ, yadidaṁ<b>—</b>kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā”ti. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">This is another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the spiritual life.” "</span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
<!-- <td><a target="_blank" href="https://voice.suttacentral.net/scv/index.html?#/sutta?search=sn45.3">mp3</a></td> -->
