<td><strong class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali">Nandiyasutta Maggasaṁyuttaṁ </strong>With Nandiya </td>
<td><div class="wordwrap"></div></td>
<td>1</td>   
<td>0</td>
<td>
<a target=_blank href=/theravada.ru/Teaching/Canon/Suttanta/Texts/sn45_10-nandiya-sutta-sv.htm>Rus</a> 
 
  <a target=_blank href=/legacy.suttacentral.net/sc/th/sn45.10.html>ไทย</a> 
<a target="_blank" href=/sc/?q=sn45.10&lang=pli-eng>SC</a> 
</td>
<td><p>
<span class="pli-lang inputscript-ISOPali" lang="pi">Seyyathidaṁ<b>—</b>sammādiṭṭhi …pe… sammāsamādhi. </span><br class="btwntrn">
<span class="eng-lang text-muted font-weight-light" lang="en">They are: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. </span>
<br class="styled">
</p></td>
